1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 54-03-02 and 54-35-16 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to periodically reconvened sessions of the legislative assembly; and to
3 provide an effective date.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 54-03-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 54-03-02. When legislative assembly meets.
8 1. The legislative assembly shall meet at the seat of government in the month of
9 December following the election of theits members thereof for organizational and
10 orientation purposes and shall thereafter recess until the time provided in
11 subsection 2.
12 2. a. The legislative assembly shall reconvene at twelve noon on the first
13 TuesdayFriday after the third day in January of the year following the
14 organizational session as provided in subsection 1 or at twelve noon on a date
15 selected by the legislative management but not earlier than January second nor
16 later than January eleventh of the year following the organizational session and,
17 following the close of business of the regular sessionfollowing Sunday, shall
18 adjournrecess subject to subdivision b and subsection 3.
19 b. The legislative assembly shall reconvene, as determined by legislative
20 management, for:
21 (1) Three consecutive natural days each month except for December, on a
22 Friday, Saturday, and Sunday; and
23 (2) In addition to the natural days reconvened under paragraph 1, up to seven
24 consecutive natural days each year.
