1 3. Notwithstanding a motion to adjourn sine die, the legislative assembly shall reconvene
2 as determined by the legislative management. The number of natural days used may
3 not exceed the number of natural days available under the constitution which have not
4 been previously used by that legislative assembly in regular session under
5 subsection 2.
6 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 54-35-16 of the North Dakota Century Code is
7 amended and reenacted as follows:
8 54-35-16. Authority to determine if legislative assembly meets.
9 The legislative management may issue a call for the legislative assembly to convene under
10 subsection 3 of section 54 - 03 - 02 after itthe legislative assembly has adjourned under
11 subsection 2 of section 54-03-02. The length of a legislative session called under this section
12 may not exceed the number of natural days available under the constitution which have not
13 been used by that legislative assembly. The legislative management may exercise this authority,
14 and the legislative assembly shall meet, regardless of whether the motion to close the regular
15 session of the legislative assembly was to recess to a time certain, adjourn to a time certain, or
16 adjourn sine die.
17 SECTION 3. EFFECTIVE DATE. This Act becomes effective on January 1, 2027.
